<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#D5E6E1"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000080" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Aldur</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Unless they get changed in the patch they are putting in at the moment - here are my findings for horses.<P>Bad<P>1.  They obscure view, making 3rd person mode almost required.<BR>2.  Difficult to turn (although turning to face a critter in this game isn't required - just a habit I got in daoc where it is required).  Also can take a little while getting upto speed - sure makes for a scary situation if ya got 10 mobs on ya backside, and ya stop to CE a harm touch ya just got, ya slowly speed up - look in reverse view and see a mob slowly closing in on ya.<BR>3.  Unable to instantly cancel spells on horseback.<BR>4.  When in spells, clicking on sit/stand doesn't take you out of spells - can get out by clicking on done - but I normally don't do that to exit spells so it is taking a little time to get used to.<P><BR>The good<P>1.  Look cool<BR>2.  Faster than sow<P>The very good probably gonna get nerfed<P>1.  There is no medding on a horse.  If you are stationary - you regain mana.  This means you can never forget to sit, you can never get auto hit for max damage because you are sitting and more importantly - any resulting agro you generally get from sitting is not created (although sometimes sit agro is useful for ghetto chanting - althought thats mostly useful indoors).<P>2.  Cast a spell, and you still regain mana.  I have not been able to test if running causes mana regen (although I think it doesn't) or if melee stops mana regen, but casting item spells causes you to regen mana.  I know this for fact.  I was down a few hps and mana, so I decided to test it and used my velious legs to heal about 600 hps.  This took me just over a minute.  Whilst this occured I recieved about half a bubble of mana, which by my reckonning is around 330 total mana.  Given that you med absolutely pathetically standing up (I remember running about for 15 mins and not even seeing a pixel).<P>I don't know if mana regen occurs when casting spells, but I can not see it differentiating between armour spells and actual spells.<P>It sure makes CH's a bit more efficent if you regain 1-2 ticks of mana whilst casting it :><P>Of course this is outside only, but its very very nice and makes a horse absolutely invaluable outside.  Go get one :></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Wisecleric</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial"> <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR>Originally posted by Aldur:<BR><B><P>The good<P>1.  Look cool<BR>2.  Faster than sow<BR></B><HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>The basic model (8-10k) do not run faster than SoW. They do not even out run j-boots. <P><BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Aldur</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">bah I meant - faster than jboots.<P>Still standing meditation is kinda nifty in itself don't ya think?</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Wisecleric</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial"> <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR>Originally posted by Aldur:<BR><B>bah I meant - faster than jboots.<P>Still standing meditation is kinda nifty in itself don't ya think?</B><HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>The basic model (8-10k) is not faster than j-boots. From test done when i got my horse its probably 20% or more slower than journeyman boots.  <P>But yes, meditation while standing is cool. <P>If you turn off your horse illusion in your setup (i turned off all models for a laggy raid i was in), click your horse on, then your j-boots, you can run a j-boot speed with no acceleration while others still see you riding a horse (and you dont have to deal with the view problems). <P></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Gniss Fleshmender</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Tested some rumors on horses today.<P>Rumor one: standing up meditate while on a horse.   <P>TRUE. Same meditate time (no mana regen other than natural) on a horse standing still as gained while sitting. (note, you can not "sit" while mounted with horses turned on.)<P>Rumor two: Meditating while moving.  <P>FALSE. Same test as I performed above, this time instead of standing still I ran in a circle on my horse. Net mana regained in the same ten minute time as previous tests: nothing. However, when I stopped to record my notes, I regained the standing meditiate ability.<P><BR>Rumor three: Meditating while fighting.<P>Unknown. I have yet to run this test, I will do it today.<P><BR>Rumor 4: Meditate while casting.<P>Unknown. If I could figure out how to cancel a spell while mounted (unable to duck), I can use my Donal brestplate to test this, as the long cast time makes for the most acuracy.<P>------------------<BR>The Drunkard of Domus Divanae<BR>Prexus</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Aldur</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">run into a few problems with this today.<P>Main one being the druid couldn't heal me or damage shield me at all, because they kept getting the out of range message - could potencially be deadly.<P>I am reasonably certain that as long as you are stationary whilst meleeing, you regain mana.<P>I was soloing bats again, and learnt a trick to maximise efficency (root, dot, then switch to dawnfire + fbss and melee - the mana loss from epic and mana belt has already been used up :>).  I definitely went up a tick of mana during melee.<P>Spell wise you definitely med whilst casting armour spells, non armour spells I can not confirm, but without a doubt you regain mana when using them.<P></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Morrun</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Another point in the "good" category: you take no fall damage.<P>Now I'm not sure if this applies to 10K falls, but I was able to charge around Mons Letalis with impunity, where falling into a canyon on foot will do over 100hp damage.  This is good enough that I'm a little worried it'll be nerfed.<P>And in the "bad" category: it's a lot harder to climb out of said canyons on horseback than on foot.<BR><P>------------------<BR>Morrun Catspaw<BR>59th level Templar of Bristlebane<BR>Albion - Death Before Dishonour!<BR>Cazic-Thule Server</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Morlife</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial"><BR>While on a horse you can not Levi (Won't be an issue if no falling damage is keep as is)<P>Can't Invise / Camo of any form while on horse back. Not an issue if buying very fast horse, but with a slow one, J-Boots and Invise (via potion or whatever) may be safer.<P>Can't go in water with a horse. Not to much of an issue since most places that you would fight in water don't allow SoW either. <P>I would exspect Nerfs to be on the way. I would also exspect them to be retroactive ( bug fixes). It was the standing that horses would only be a graphical and speed enhancement. They were to offer no other abilities. So while I hope it stays, the mana regen may be a bug. <P>If that is the case then they should fix it so Levi, Invise, Water can be done with a horse, and Speed / Graphic is the only change.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Qanimaru</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">10K falls will still kill you even on a horse. Seems you take no damage from falls up until you reach the "this fall should kill anyone" level at which point it does. I'm sure that was put in to stop people from using horses to get down into pits on a horse that they normally couldn't have jumped safely into.<P>Qanimaru...<BR></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
</FONT>
